d to fight terror in the US... many may think it is an infringement on civil rights. Whatever the case may be, it has changed the way we live.<br><br>I know that many will contend that similar measures were taken in the 40's during WWII, and to some degree you would be right. Yet those changes were legislated, voted and signed (to my recollection). These recent 'changes' are not and have not been: debated, voted on..anything! And honestly I have no fooking clue as to how quickly something of this scale and magnitude can &quot;change&quot; overnight! WTH?<br><br>Let me give what little information I have in regards to what powers or authority the FBI-CIA had prior to these changes... Please step in and correct me if I'm wrong.: <br><br>The CIA could never be used to spy on domestic affairs..now they can.<br><br>The FBI could not 'snoop' or monitor your personal PC, home, finances unless they had the equivalent of a search warrant...now they can. Many think that they already had the authority to do so, and perhaps the technology, but the law did not allow it accept under certain guidelines.... now they can snoop you freely at anytime for whatever reason.<br><br>The FBI could not enter a church or 'holy place' unless they have substantial evidence that criminal activity was already taking place....now they can spy and enter at will to monitor what they perceive as perhaps 'potential' criminal activity.<br><br>Now, many will contend that &quot;these are new threats..we live in different times where this is necessary&quot; and &quot;I have nothing to hide...search away! I hope you catch those bastards!&quot; But what I personally feel is that we are still under attack and the &quot;new measures&quot; are an extension of the terrorists attack in that we are loosing freedom. <br><br>These new measures, as they are called, are a crap-shoot at best. There is still NOTHING being done about how they communicate between one-another. The size of the government is growing instead of getting smaller...and as many may know full and well... that if you increase the size of your business... the harder it becomes to manage. So what really have we accomplished with this revamp? I am guessing that they hope that with the 'un-tieing' of the hands of these departments they will be able to find suspected terrorism in the making...instead of after it happens or too close to the time its happens (if it ever happens again).?<br><br>Then we must ask ourselves.. &quot;what is a terrorist?&quot;  I mean, we know what kind of terrorists destroyed our buildings killing many many innocent people, but are there different types of terrorist that could 'potentially' do harm? All depends on what  they / we view as 'harm'.<br><br>&quot;HAHAHAHAH!  Look at those stupid American's!!  LOL!  National ID cards, government ran airport security, FBI-CIA monitoring EVERYONE and they still call it the 'land of the free'!!  ROFL!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;Give me liberty, or give me death!!&quot;  poe'lease!<br> <p><B><font color=#00dd00>Rh</font><font color=#00cc00>ea</font><font color=#00bb00>to</font><font color=#00aa00>n</font> <font color=#009900>St</font><font color=#009900>or</font><font color=#008800>m</font><font color=#007700>ca</font><font color=#006600>st</font><BR><font color=#00dd00>55</font><font color=#00cc00>th</font> <font color=#00bb00>Se</font><font color=#00aa00>as</font><font color=#009900>on</font> <font color=#008800>Ma</font><font color=#007700>gi</font><font color=#006600>ci</font><font color=#005500>an</font><BR><font color=#00dd00>Co</font><font color=#00cc00>un</font><font color=#00bb00>ci</font><font color=#00aa00>l o</font><font color=#009900>f U</font><font color=#008800>nb</font><font color=#007700>ro</font><font color=#006600>ke</font><font color=#005500>n H</font><font color=#004400>on</font><font color=#003300>or</font></B><BR><a href="http://unbrokenhonor.homestead.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://unbr