 with Rheaton on something! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>In Australia, the government recently attemptted to introduce legislation to grant ASIO (kinda like the FBI) the right to detain people without charges for 48hrs, INDEFINATELY RENEWABLE, with no right to a lawyer or even right to silence! Refusing to speak could result in a 5 year jail sentance. They also wanted to allow banning of organisations based on VERY loosely worded definitions of terrorism, which could result in 20 years in jail for being a member of or donating money to, oh say, Greenpeace would easily fit the definitions provided.<br><br>I'm very concerned that many of the measures being introduced in countries around the world in the name of the &quot;War on Terrorism&quot; are grossly impinging on people's rights, and in many cases will have little if any effect on terrorism. For example, some attempts to strengthen restrictions on cryptography. Trying to reel back and keep from terrorists information which is already freely available to them, and which can't feasibly be &quot;vanished&quot; seems a foolish endevour in the extreme. <p>----------------------------------<br>[59 Troubadour]<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78662">Maeri</a>&lt;Anlah'Shok&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulithahntalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lith Ahntalon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/1/02 7:37:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title