inal post, you are much MISTAKEN. You have completely taken my post wrongly. The examples you give are of a freedom that is brought about by anarchy …not democracy!<br><br>&quot;Laws must &quot;limit freedom&quot; as you would call it. Although I still feel absoluty free to do what I want in my life in the US.&quot; Feel free to your individual rights to privacy?<br><br>The point is that IF WE TRADE SAFETY FOR FREEDOM... we no longer have freedom. If we allow laws to pass, or changes to be made, that prohibit or infringe upon our freedoms in the name of self-preservation, then we have gained is self-preservation and what we have lost is freedom. What part of that do you not understand?<br><br>I have my personal grips with certain laws and their constitutionality, but the BIGGER point I was trying to make with the original post was... how much?  How much are you willing to give up to be safe?<br><br>I guess it all depends on your definition of freedom...right?<br><br> <p><B><font color=#00dd00>Rh</font><font color=#00cc00>ea</font><font color=#00bb00>to</font><font color=#00aa00>n</font> <font color=#009900>St</font><font color=#009900>or</font><font color=#008800>m</font><font color=#007700>ca</font><font color=#006600>st</font><BR><font color=#00dd00>55</font><font color=#00cc00>th</font> <font color=#00bb00>Se</font><font color=#00aa00>as</font><font color=#009900>on</font> <font color=#008800>Ma</font><font color=#007700>gi</font><font color=#006600>ci</font><font color=#005500>an</font><BR><font color=#00dd00>Co</font><font color=#00cc00>un</font><font color=#00bb00>ci</font><font color=#00aa00>l o</font><font color=#009900>f U</font><font color=#008800>nb</font><font color=#007700>ro</font><font color=#006600>ke</font><font color=#005500>n H</font><font color=#004400>on</font><font color=#003300>or</font></B><BR><a href="http://unbrokenhonor.homestead.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://unbrokenhonor.homestead.com/files/rheaton5.jpg"